episodes.title: What to expect from latest Epstein files release
episodes.description:

episodes.title: What we've learned from the Epstein files released so far
episodes.description:
The Justice Department began releasing thousands of records related to the Jeffrey Epstein case on Friday as part of a law President Trump signed in November. As more files get released, here's what we've learned so far. 

0:00 DOJ releases inital trove of Epstein files
4:12 Documents, photos released as part of Epstein files
8:46 At least 14 Epstein files disappear from DOJ's website
11:46 More than 10,000 new Epstein files released by DOJ
12:17 Trump makes first public comments since Epstein files release

episodes.title: Rep. Ro Khanna says DOJ Epstein files release was a "slap in the face" to survivors
episodes.description:
Reps. Ro Khanna, a California Democrat, and Thomas Massie, a Kentucky Republican, who pushed for the Justice Department to release the Jeffrey Epstein files, said the problem with the release isn't that it's "taking too long" and but that Friday's release is a "slap in the face of survivors."

episodes.title: Prince Andrew to lose real estate, titles, in unprecedented move from Buckingham Palace
episodes.description:
King Charles' brother, Prince Andrew, is being stripped of his royal titles, Buckingham Palace announced Thursday. He will now be known as Andrew Mountbatten Windsor. CBS News' Imtiaz Tyab and Julian Payne have more.
